            "answer_text": "A2A. A metal/ion can show paramagnetism only if it has unpaired electrons. In case , all electrons are paired it will show diamagnetic behaviour. Here, sodium has an unpaired electron (3s1) which is lost when sodium ion is formed. So, there is no question of sodium ion showing paramagnetic behaviour. ",
